de.mrapp.android.adapter.list.filterable

Interface FilterableListAdapter<DataType>

  • Type Parameters:
    DataType - The type of the adapter's underlying data
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ListAdapter<DataType>, MultipleChoiceListAdapter<DataType>, SelectableListAdapter<DataType>, SingleChoiceListAdapter<DataType>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractEnableStateListAdapter, AbstractFilterableListAdapter, AbstractItemStateListAdapter, AbstractListAdapter, AbstractSelectableListAdapter, AbstractSortableListAdapter, ListAdapterImplementation, MultipleChoiceListAdapterImplementation, SingleChoiceListAdapterImplementation

    public interface FilterableListAdapter<DataType>
    Defines the interface, an adapter, whose underlying data is managed as a filterable list of arbitrary items, must implement. Such an adapter's purpose is to provide the underlying data for visualization using a AbsListView widget.
    Since:
    0.1.0

    • Method Detail

      • applyFilter

        boolean applyFilter(java.lang.String query,
                    int flags)
        Filters the adapter's items by using a specific query, if no filter using the same query has been applied yet. If the adapter's underlying data does not implement the interface Filterable a FilteringNotSupportedException will be thrown. This method can be called multiple times without resetting the filtering, which causes the filtered item to be filtered once more.
        Parameters:
        query - The query, which should be used to filter the items, as a String. The query may not be null
        flags - The flags, which should be used to filter the item, as an Integer value, or 0, if no flags should be used
        Returns:
        True, if the filter has been applied, false otherwise

      • applyFilter

        boolean applyFilter(java.lang.String query,
                    int flags,
                    Filter<DataType> filter)
        Filters the adapter's items by using a specific query and a filter, which is used to apply the query on the single items, if no filter using the same query has been applied yet. This method can be called multiple times without resetting the filtering, which causes the filtered items to be filtered once more.
        Parameters:
        query - The query, which should be used to filter the items, as a String. The query may not be null
        flags - The flags, which should be used to filter the items, as an Integer value, or 0, if no flags should be used
        filter - The filter, which should be used to apply the given query on the adapter's items, as an instance of the type Filter . The filter may not be null
        Returns:
        True, if the filter has been applied, false otherwise

      • resetFilter

        boolean resetFilter(java.lang.String query,

        Resets the filter, which uses a specific query.
        Parameters:

        flags - The flags of the filter, which should be reseted, as an Integer value
        Returns:
        True, if the filter has been reseted, false otherwise
